            </section>
        </ul>
        
        <section>
            <h2><u>Cui</u>sine</h2>
            <p>Western Maharashtra is known for its delicious and diverse cuisine:</p>
        </section>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Puran Poli:</strong> A sweet flatbread stuffed with a mixture of jaggery and split chickpeas, popular during festivals.</li>
            <p>Puran Poli is a traditional Maharashtrian dish enjoyed during festivals and special occasions. It is made with a dough of wheat flour stuffed with a sweet filling of jaggery and cooked lentils, served with ghee or milk. This delectable treat is a favorite among families and represents the rich culinary traditions of the region.</p>

            <section>
                <img src="/Images-2/Puran Poli.jpeg" alt="Puran Poli" width="500px">
            </section>

            <li><strong>
                Kolhapuri Chicken:</strong> A popular street food that consists of a spicy potato fritter served in a bun.</li>
            <p>
                Kolhapuri Chicken is a renowned dish from Western Maharashtra, celebrated for its fiery flavors and rich spices. This traditional chicken curry is characterized by its robust heat, which comes from a unique blend of spices such as red chili, garlic, and garam masala. The chicken is slow-cooked in a thick, flavorful gravy, allowing the spices to meld beautifully and infuse the meat. Typically served with steamed rice or chapati, it’s a favorite among spice lovers seeking a hearty and satisfying meal.</p>
                <p>Originating from the Kolhapur region, this dish reflects the culinary heritage of Maharashtra, where the use of spices is both an art and a tradition. Local chefs often pride themselves on their secret spice blends, making each preparation unique. Kolhapuri Chicken is often accompanied by sides like bhakri (a type of flatbread) or sol kadhi (a refreshing coconut milk drink), enhancing the dining experience. Whether enjoyed at a family gathering or a local restaurant, Kolhapuri Chicken is a must-try for anyone wanting to savor the authentic flavors of Western Maharashtra.</p>

            <section>
                <img src="https://www.indianhealthyrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/kolhapuri-chicken-recipe.jpg" width="600px">
            </section>

            <li><strong>Misal Pav:</strong> A spicy curry served with bread, known for its bold flavors.</li>
            <p>Misal Pav is a beloved dish from Western Maharashtra, known for its vibrant flavors and hearty ingredients. This spicy curry is primarily made from sprouted lentils, cooked with a medley of aromatic spices and topped with a tangy mix of onions, tomatoes, and coriander. Served with soft bread rolls, or pav, it creates a delightful combination that is both filling and satisfying. Often garnished with crispy chivda (a crunchy snack) and a squeeze of lemon, Misal Pav is a favorite for breakfast or as a snack throughout the day.</p>
            <p>
                The dish reflects the region’s rich culinary heritage and is popular at roadside stalls and eateries. Each vendor often has their own unique recipe, resulting in a delightful variety of flavors and textures. Misal Pav not only showcases the bold spices of Maharashtrian cuisine but also embodies the communal dining culture, as friends and families often gather around to share this iconic meal. Whether enjoyed at a bustling street stall or a local restaurant, Misal Pav is a must-try for anyone exploring the culinary delights of Western Maharashtra.
            </p>

